{"id":17683,"date":"2014-01-21T19:02:02","date_gmt":"2014-01-21T15:02:02","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=17683"},"modified":"2019-05-15T18:03:25","modified_gmt":"2019-05-15T14:03:25","slug":"umar-apostasy-riddah-murtad","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/21\/umar-apostasy-riddah-murtad\/","title":{"rendered":"Umar on Apostasy: I did not command it, I was not pleased"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Muhammad ibn al-Qari reported: A man came to Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, from Abu Musa al-Ashari. Umar asked him about the people and he informed him. Then, Umar said, \u201cDo you have any recent news?\u201d Abu Musa said, \u201cYes, a man turned back to unbelief after his Islam.\u201d Umar said, \u201cWhat have you done with him?\u201d Abu Musa said, \u201cWe let him approach and we struck his neck.\u201d Umar said, \u201cDid you not imprison him for three days and feed him each day with bread and call him to repent and return to the command of Allah?\u201d Then, Umar said, \u201cO Allah, I was not present and I did not command it and I was not pleased when I heard it!\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a&#8217; 1397<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan<\/i> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u062f\u0650\u0645\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0631\u064e